# SSH/SFTP shell account

A shell account refers to a text-mode interface where commands can be run interactively. All OCF accounts include shell account access. You can access your shell account over an encrypted connection in the OCF lab or remotely via SSH/SFTP.

We support the following commonly used shell account tools (to name a few):

*   Subversion, Git, and Mercurial: version control
*   cron and at: execute commands on a periodic or scheduled basis 
*   vim and emacs: powerful and extensible text editors

Most SSH/SFTP clients will prompt you to accept an unknown key when you first connect. Our SSH fingerprint can be used to verify that you're connecting to the correct server:

    2048 55:0a:e3:4f:4b:2c:15:f8:d4:7d:f9:93:bf:a0:41:21 tsunami.ocf.berkeley.edu (RSA)
    1024 7e:19:bc:fd:b5:cd:5c:e3:42:a4:a5:74:eb:ce:5d:2e tsunami.ocf.berkeley.edu (DSA)
    256  a2:4b:d5:17:43:2e:a7:ea:50:d7:ab:1f:63:45:a9:6c tsunami.ocf.berkeley.edu (ECDSA)

## SSH

Your shell account can be controlled remotely using [SSH](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secure_Shell). The server name is <tt>ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu</tt> (<tt>tsunami</tt>).

On Unix-like (e.g., GNU/Linux and Mac OS X) systems, enter in the terminal:

    ssh username@ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu

On Windows systems, use [PuTTY](http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/) (you'll want to [download](http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/download.html) putty.exe):

* Host Name: <tt>ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu</tt>
* Port: 22 (default)

Alternatively, use [FireSSH](https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/firessh/) (Firefox addon). Once installed, simply access the following URL: [ssh://ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu](ssh://ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu)

## SFTP

You can transfer files to your account using [SFTP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SSH_File_Transfer_Protocol). SFTP is accessed over SSH, but you'll probably need to use another program, like [FireFTP](https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/fireftp/) (Firefox addon), [WinSCP](http://winscp.net/) (Windows), [Cyberduck](http://cyberduck.ch/) (Mac OS X, Windows), or Nautilus (GNU/Linux).

If using Firefox and FireFTP is installed, simply access the following URL:
[sftp://ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu](sftp://ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu)

Otherwise, use the following information in your SFTP client.

* Protocol: SFTP (or SSH)
* Host Name: <tt>ssh.ocf.berkeley.edu</tt>
* Port: 22 (default)
